com.group4.ist412.icare412

Class HTTPServer.MultipartInputStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.InputStream
      • java.io.FilterInputStream
        • com.group4.ist412.icare412.HTTPServer.MultipartInputStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable
    Enclosing class:
    HTTPServer

    public static class HTTPServer.MultipartInputStream
extends FilterInputStream
    The MultipartInputStream decodes an InputStream whose data has a "multipart/*" content type (see RFC 2046), providing the underlying data of its various parts.

    The InputStream methods (e.g. read()) relate only to the current part, and the nextPart() method advances to the beginning of the next part.

      • nextPart

        public boolean nextPart()
                 throws IOException
        Advances the stream position to the beginning of the next part. Data read before calling this method for the first time is the preamble, and data read after this method returns false is the epilogue.
        Returns:
        true if successful, or false if there are no more parts
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurs

      • fill

        protected boolean fill()
                throws IOException
        Fills the buffer with more data from the underlying stream.
        Returns:
        true if there is available data for the current part, or false if the current part's end has been reached
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurs or the input format is invalid
